<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph_with_headers', :locals => { contents: ["<strong>If you made payments <u>after</u> the effective date of your plan termination or cancellation, and those funds have not already been refunded to you, you can call your health insurance company at the numbers listed above to request a refund.</strong> If the plan refuses to provide the refund, you can contact the Department of Insurance, Securities, and Banking Consumer Services Division at <a href='disb.complaints@dc.gov'>disb.complaints@dc.gov</a> or (202) 727-8000. You can also submit a complaint online at <a href='http://dcforms.dc.gov/webform/consumer-complaint-form-disb-0'>http://dcforms.dc.gov/webform/consumer-complaint-form-disb-0</a>."], heading:'Refunds', sub_heading: ''} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph_with_headers', :locals => { contents: ["If you are receiving this notice between November 1 and January 31, Open Enrollment is still open and you can still pick a plan. This SEP denial only affects your ability to receive an early start date rather than a regular start date for your plan. Additionally, as mentioned in the “Other Coverage You May Have” section above, it does not affect coverage you have already enrolled in through DC Health Link <u>and that has not been terminated/cancelled</u> for any reason (for example non-payment or late payment)."], heading:'Open Enrollment Season', sub_heading: ''} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => { content: "Otherwise, if you are receiving this notice after January 31, the Open Enrollment season for the current calendar year is closed. The 2016 Open Enrollment Season ended on January 31, 2016."} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => { content: "This denial notice indicates you cannot enroll in a private insurance plan though DC Health Link because you do not qualify for a special enrollment period."} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph_with_headers', :locals => { contents: ["The enrollment period for Medicaid never closes. A person can apply for Medicaid coverage through DC Health Link at any time of the year by completing an application for financial assistance.  Nothing in this decision impacts the eligibility of anyone in your household who has already been determined eligible for Medicaid or may become eligible in the future."], heading:'Medicaid Enrollment', sub_heading: ''} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph_with_headers', :locals => { contents: ["If you disagree with this determination, you have the right to appeal to an independent administrative law judge. You may request an appeal by phone, in person, online, and by mail. You must request an appeal <strong>by «Appeal_Deadline»</strong>. The DC Health Benefit Exchange Authority will work to resolve your appeal as quickly as possible, but appeals can take between 30 and 90 days to resolve. <strong>See the insert for more information on your appeal rights</strong>. 45 C.F.R. §155.520."], heading:'If You Think We Made a Mistake', sub_heading: ''} %>